page.title: 08Flora and Fauna.
page.content: Country area much grassland,hedgerows and grassy lanes.Dykes,canals and river provide habitat for wild life. TREES,mainly ash,oak,hawthorn,willow and elm. MAMMALS,rabbits,hares,fox,voles,stoat, weasel,shrews,fieldmice. BIRDS,blackbird,sparrows,thrush,crow, starling,chaffinch,bullfinch,magpie, goldfinch,goldcrest,wren,pigeon,dove, rooks,owls,woodpecker,pheasant,plover, partridge,gulls,fieldfares,swallow, housemartin. WATERFOWL,mallard,coot,grebe,moorhen, swan,heron. A vast variety of hedgerow plants and wild flowers,honeysuckle,wild rose, bramble,dog daisies,white violets,cow- slip,celandine,mlik maids,primose. Canal and dyke banks have abundant insect life;areas of preservation include trees and grassland.
